'''Silas Carson''' is an English actor who played [[Nute Gunray]], [[Lott Dod]], [[Ki-Adi-Mundi]] and [[Antidar Williams]], the [[pilot]] who died at the beginning of [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|Episode I]].

Outside of Star Wars, Carson also made a guest appearance on the UK series [[Wikipedia:Hustle (TV series)|''Hustle'']], [[Wikipedia:Strike Back (TV series)|''Strike Back'']], [[Wikipedia:The Bill (TV series)|''The Bill'']] and [[Wikipedia:Spooks|''Spooks'']]. He provided the voice of the Adherents of the Repeated Meme for the [[Wikipedia:Doctor Who|''Doctor Who'']] episode [[Wikipedia:The End of the World (Doctor Who)|''The End of the World'']] and voices the alien race Ood in the episodes [[Wikipedia:The Impossible Planet|''The Impossible Planet'']], [[Wikipedia:Planet of the Ood|''Planet of the Ood'']], [[Wikipedia:The End of Time|''The End of Time'']] and ''[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doctor_Who_(series_13) The Flux]''.

He also appeared in the films ''Fever Pitch'', ''Boogie Woogie'' (with [[Christopher Lee]]) and ''Hidalgo'', and in the television shows ''Supply & Demand'', ''How Not to Live Your Life'', and [[Wikipedia:Cold Lazarus|''Cold Lazarus'']].

